    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "On-call runbook",
      "id": 6,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 12,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 15
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### \ud83d\udea8 Page received \u2014 what to do\n\n**Step 1. Confirm the drift phase** (top-left).\nIf `BASELINE` \u2192 false positive, check Prometheus rule.\nIf `INCIDENT` \u2192 keep reading.\n\n**Step 2. Compare model version** (next panel) with the version 24h ago.\nIf changed \u2192 provider rolled silent update. **Pin model snapshot** in your code.\n\n**Step 3. Which RAGAS metric dropped?**\n- `faithfulness \u2193`, others ok \u2192 model is hallucinating. Likely cause: model swap, prompt regression.\n- `context_precision \u2193` \u2192 retrieval is broken. Check embedding model version, vector index size.\n- `relevancy \u2193` only on some intents \u2192 docs are stale. Trigger reindex.\n\n**Step 4. Is refusal rate up?**\nIf yes \u2192 check `safety_violations` panel \u2014 possible prompt-injection wave.\n\n**Step 5. Is cost up but quality ok?**\nProvider routed to expensive variant. Slack the team, not page.\n\n**Step 6. Mitigation order**:\n1. **Pin** previous model snapshot (`model: gpt-4o-2024-05-13`).\n2. **Roll back** prompt to last known good (registry).\n3. **Increase eval sampling** (5% \u2192 50%) for 30 min.\n4. If RAG-related \u2014 **rebuild index** with old embedder.\n\n**Step 7. After incident**: add the new failure mode to golden dataset."
      }
    },
